# Vercel Web Analytics Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Keyword Cockpit project following the latest official Vercel documentation.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **Installed**: `@vercel/analytics@^2.0.1`
- **Method**: npm install
- **Files Modified**: 
  - `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
  - `package-lock.json` - Created with locked dependency versions

### 2. Analytics Integration
Added Vercel Web Analytics script to all 7 HTML pages following the vanilla/static site implementation pattern from the official documentation:

**Modified HTML Files:**
- `public/index.html` - Main keyword analysis page
- `public/about.html` - About page
- `public/admin.html` - Admin dashboard
- `public/blog-index.html` - Blog index page
- `public/changelog.html` - Changelog page
- `public/guide.html` - Guide page
- `public/radar.html` - Radar page

**Implementation Details:**
Each HTML file now includes the following scripts before the closing `</body>` tag:
```html
<script>
  window.va = window.va || function () { (window.vaq = window.vaq || []).push(arguments); };
</script>
<script defer src="/_vercel/insights/script.js"></script>
```

This implementation follows the Vercel documentation for vanilla/static sites and ensures:
- Analytics are loaded asynchronously (defer attribute)
- The `window.va` function is available for tracking
- All page views are automatically tracked once deployed

## Framework Detection
The project is a **static site** using vanilla HTML/JavaScript with Vercel serverless functions for the API. The vanilla/static site implementation pattern was used as specified in the Vercel Web Analytics quickstart guide.

## Next Steps
After deployment to Vercel:
1. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Analytics section)
2. Verify analytics are working by checking browser Network tab for requests to `/_vercel/insights/*`
3. Monitor the analytics dashboard for visitor data
4. Analytics will be fully operational once the project is deployed and Web Analytics is enabled in the Vercel dashboard

## Testing
- ✅ All 7 HTML files successfully updated with analytics scripts
- ✅ Package.json and package-lock.json properly updated
- ✅ No syntax errors introduced
- ✅ Existing functionality preserved
- ✅ All changes staged for commit

## Notes
- This is a static site project, so the vanilla JavaScript implementation was used
- The analytics script uses the standard Vercel path `/_vercel/insights/script.js`
- No additional configuration needed - analytics will work automatically after deployment
- The implementation is non-invasive and doesn't affect existing functionality
